It seems that challenges in this area are already starting to emerge. Due to the FAA's stance on certain medications, I may have difficulty obtaining a medical certificate.
This is not impossible, but it requires a lot of time and a lot of additional work.
Although this is somewhat discouraging, it's just another problem that needs to be addressed, and it seems "definitely" solvable at the moment. The catch is that it will require a significant amount of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges I'm about to face:
The FAA doesn't like ADHD. If you're taking medication for ADHD, you definitely won't get a medical certificate.
